org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel

Interface ConditionalFormattingRule

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DifferentialStyleProvider
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HSSFConditionalFormattingRule, XSSFConditionalFormattingRule 

    public interface ConditionalFormattingRule
extends DifferentialStyleProvider
    Represents a description of a conditional formatting rule(表示条件格式规则的描述)

      • getConditionFilterType

        ConditionFilterType getConditionFilterType()
        This is null if

        getConditionType() != ConditionType.FILTER

        This is always ConditionFilterType.FILTER for HSSF rules of type ConditionType.FILTER.

        For XSSF filter rules, this will indicate the specific type of filter.

        (如果getConditionType（）！=对于类型为ConditionType.FILTER的HSSF规则，此值始终为ConditionFilterType. FILTER。对于XSSF过滤器规则，这将指示过滤器的特定类型。)
        Returns:
        filter type for filter rules, or null if not a filter rule.(过滤器规则的过滤器类型，如果不是过滤器规则，则为空。)

      • getFilterConfiguration

        ConditionFilterData getFilterConfiguration()
        This is null if

        getConditionFilterType() == null

        This means it is always null for HSSF, which does not define the extended condition types.

        This object contains the additional configuration information for XSSF filter conditions.

        (如果getConditionFilterType（）==空，则此值为空这意味着对于HSSF，它始终为空，HSSF不定义扩展条件类型。此对象包含XSSF筛选条件的其他配置信息。)
        Returns:
        the Filter Configuration Data, or null if there isn't any(过滤器配置数据，如果没有，则为空)

      • getComparisonOperation

        byte getComparisonOperation()
        The comparison function used when the type of conditional formatting is set to ConditionType.CELL_VALUE_IS

        MUST be a constant from ComparisonOperator

        (条件格式类型设置为ConditionType时使用的比较函数。CELL_UTE_IS必须是ComparisonOperator中的常数)
        Returns:
        the conditional format operator(条件格式运算符)

      • getFormula1

        java.lang.String getFormula1()
        The formula used to evaluate the first operand for the conditional formatting rule.

        If the condition type is ConditionType.CELL_VALUE_IS, this field is the first operand of the comparison. If type is ConditionType.FORMULA, this formula is used to determine if the conditional formatting is applied.

        If comparison type is ConditionType.FORMULA the formula MUST be a Boolean function

        (用于计算条件格式规则的第一个操作数的公式。如果条件类型为ConditionType. CY_UTE_IS，则此字段是比较的第一个操作数。如果类型为ConditionType.FORMULA，则使用此公式来确定是否应用条件格式。如果比较类型为ConditionType.FORMULA，则公式必须是布尔函数)
        Returns:
        the first formula(第一个公式)

      • getFormula2

        java.lang.String getFormula2()
        The formula used to evaluate the second operand of the comparison when comparison type is ConditionType.CELL_VALUE_IS and operator is either ComparisonOperator.BETWEEN or ComparisonOperator.NOT_BETWEEN(当比较类型为ConditionType. CY_UTE_IS且运算符为ComparisonOperator.BETWEEN或ComparisonOperator.NOT_BETWEEN时，用于计算比较的第二个操作数的公式)
        Returns:
        the second formula(第二个公式)

      • getText

        java.lang.String getText()
        XSSF rules store textual condition values as an attribute and also as a formula that needs shifting. Using the attribute is simpler/faster. HSSF rules don't have this and return null. We can fall back on the formula for those (AFAIK).(XSSF规则将文本条件值存储为属性和需要转换的公式。使用该属性更简单/更快。HSSF规则不具有此功能并返回空。我们可以依靠这些公式（AFAIK）。)
        Returns:
        condition text if it exists, or null(条件文本（如果存在）或空)

      • getPriority

        int getPriority()
        The priority of the rule, if defined, otherwise 0.

        If priority is 0, just use definition order, as that's how older HSSF rules are evaluated.

        For XSSF, this should always be set. For HSSF, only newer style rules have this set, older ones will return 0.

        If a rule is created but not yet added to a sheet, this value may not be valid.

        (规则的优先级（如果已定义），否则为0。如果优先级为0，则只需使用定义顺序，因为这就是旧HSSF规则的评估方式。对于XSSF，应始终设置此设置。对于HSSF，只有较新的样式规则才有此设置，较旧的样式规则将返回0。如果规则已创建但尚未添加到工作表中，则此值可能无效。)
        Returns:
        rule priority(规则优先级)

      • getStopIfTrue

        boolean getStopIfTrue()
        Always true for HSSF rules, optional flag for XSSF rules. See Excel help for more.(对于HSSF规则始终正确，对于XSSF规则来说是可选的标志。请参阅Excel帮助了解更多信息。)
        Returns:
        true if conditional formatting rule processing stops when this one is true, false if not(如果条件格式规则处理在此为真时停止，则为真，否则为假)
        See Also:
        Microsoft Excel help
